<p>iFixit has a set of instructions (
<a href="https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/iMac+Intel+27-Inch+EMC+2429+Hard+Drive+Replacement/7555">https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/iMac+Intel+27-Inch+EMC+2429+Hard+Drive+Replacement/7555</a>), but you donâ€™t need so many steps to change the drive.
The non-obvious step is how to open the case. It is held in with magnets
and you need a glass lifter remove the front glass assembly. Mine was from
Harbour Freight <a href="https://www.harborfreight.com/dual-cup-suction-lifter-46134.html">https://www.harborfreight.com/dual-cup-suction-lifter-46134.html</a>.</p>

